==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Disbench
<hw>Dis*bench"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To
drive from a bench or seat.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Eng. Law)</fld> <def>To deprive (a bencher) of his
privileges.</def> <rj><au>Mozley & W.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Disbend</ent>⟦br⟧
